500|$|In June 1537 in {{his will}} among many provisions, Francesco {{returned}} Lisa's dowry to her, gave her personal clothing and jewelry and provided for her future. Upon entrusting her care to their daughter Ludovica and, should she be incapable, his son Bartolomeo, Francesco wrote, [...] "Given the affection and love of the <b>testator</b> towards Mona Lisa, his beloved wife; in consideration {{of the fact that}} Lisa has always acted with a noble spirit and as a faithful wife; wishing that she shall have all she needs…".|$|E
